.TH A2CERTRENEW 1 "2026-07-05" "a2tools 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
a2certrenew \- force a manual \fBcertbot renew\fR run
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B a2certrenew
.RI [ certbot\-flags ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBa2certrenew\fR is a thin wrapper over \fBcertbot renew\fR.
It exists so the run can be logged to
\fB/var/log/a2tools/a2certrenew.log\fR and so the operator does not
have to remember the verb.
.PP
Routine renewals are NOT triggered by this script: \fBcertbot\fR's own
systemd timer (shipped with the \fBcertbot\fR package) runs
\fBcertbot renew\fR twice a day. The
\fB/etc/letsencrypt/renewal\-hooks/deploy/a2tools\fR deploy hook
reloads Apache and updates the \fBa2tools\fR domains database after
every successful renewal.
.PP
Any extra arguments are passed through to \fBcertbot renew\fR, for
example:
.PP
.RS
.nf
sudo a2certrenew \-\-force\-renewal
sudo a2certrenew \-\-cert\-name example.com
sudo a2certrenew \-\-dry\-run
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
The exit status of \fBcertbot renew\fR is returned unchanged.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /var/log/a2tools/a2certrenew.log
Per\-run log of every manual invocation.
.TP
.I /etc/letsencrypt/renewal\-hooks/deploy/a2tools
Symlink to the \fBa2tools\fR deploy hook (installed by the package's
postinst script).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR a2sitemgr (1),
.BR certbot (1),
.BR certbot.timer (8)
